briefdescription.para: Get a value that indicates if this is a valid Survey object.

detaileddescription.para: A valid survey has a client, county, job number, and description at the very least.

briefdescription.para: Populates the objects for this survey with values from the database.

detaileddescription.para: Gets the survey's Client, County, Realtor, TitleCompany, and any files associated with it.

briefdescription.para: Add a new file to the associated file list.
Adds the files to the associated file list if they are not already present.
Overwrites the files list to be the specified files instead.

parameterdescription.para: The files to set as the new Files list.

briefdescription.para: Remove a file, if it exists, from the associated file list.
Remove all files in files from Files.

parameterdescription.para: The collection of files to remove.

briefdescription.para: Clear this survey's associated files and file ids.
Add a new file id to the id list.
Remove a file id from the id list.
Parses a string containing notes and times into the appropiate dictionary in this class.

detaileddescription.para: A note is specified by a dateTime in ticks (i.e., 637539336310000000) followed by a string; these two components are seperated by /**/

parameterdescription.para: The string containing the notes and time information.

briefdescription.para: Handles insertion of this survey and any files associated with it.

simplesect.para: A DatabaseError with the result of the Insert operation.

briefdescription.para: Handles updating this survey and any files associated with it as well. If there is a file with an ID of 0 (meaning it hasn't been inserted yet), inserts it.

simplesect.para: A DatabaseError with the result of the Update operation.

briefdescription.para: Delete this survey from the database, along with the associated files and billing line items.

simplesect.para: A DatabaseError with the result of the Delete operation.
